 MBOMBELA –  According to police spokesman, Col Mtsholi Bhembe, the woman allegedly stabbed her 17-year-old son at Calcutta, near Hazyview in the early hours of Tuesday morning. “It is alleged that the mother and son had an argument over an identity document, before she stabbed the boy to death. He was found by community members lying on the street. Police were called to the scene and are investigating a murder case.” Police request anyone with information that may lead to the arrest of the suspect to contact Lt Col Dudu Shabangu on
082-469-2569 or the Crime Stop number 086-001-0111. In another incident, a 17-year-old girl was allegedly raped by her ex-boyfriend on Tuesday.
It is reported that the girl was on her way to school with a friend when she met her ex-boyfriend along the way. He allegedly pointed a firearm at her and threatened to kill her if she did not comply with his instructions. He then dragged her to his house and raped her. The suspect is still at large and police are requesting anyone with information concerning his whereabouts to contact
WO Ekson Maluka on 082-469-2940.